[Student "S"]
{The 2NT response to a Weak Two opening is a wonderful tool. You can learn a lot about 
partner's hand and you are absolutely certain that it will not be passed out.

In this Deal NORTH has a huge hand and SOUTH opens 2\D. 
There are a lot of approaches NORTH might try, but the simplest is to start with 2NT.

When SOUTH shows \D A K Q x x x NORTH has an easy 6NT bid.}

[Event ""]
[Site ""]
[Date ""]
[Board "3"]
[Dealer "E"]
[Vulnerable "EW"]
[Deal "E:AQ9752.K3.852.73 T4.T85.QJ3.J9864 KJ6.AQJ42.964.A5 83.976.AKT7.KQT2"]
[Declarer "E"]
[Contract "4S"]
[Result ""]
[Auction "E"]
2S pass 2NT pass 3H pass 4S pass pass pass
[BCFlags "1f"]
[RotationNote "Board 3, chOption: E, chBasis: S, basisKind:Declarer, nOption:1, nBasis: 2, nRot: 3, useStandardVul: true"]
[BoardVersionToken "c147c948d4c7a1874470e044ed22705be5eec047adf5c9cada77c8f5997b4faf"]
[Category "Partnership Bidding"]
[Difficulty "intermediate"]
[SkillPath "partnership_bidding/weak_twos"]
[Student "S"]
{WEST is unsure whether to bid game or not. So she temporizes with 2NT.

EAST shows an above average hand plus a high card in \Hs. 

WEST is no longer unsure, so she bids 4\S.}

